EMC/EMI are difficult tasks that many electronics engineers are
facing. Often due to space and cost constraints, some so called golden
rules can not be followed 100% and sometimes you just do not know
where the noise comes from. Experiences defintely count here.

I'd like to seek advice from the experienced engineers here on the
topics of immunity, in paticular, Electrical Fast Transient (also
called burst), Conducted Immunity (CI, sometimes called Current
Injection) and Radiated Immunity (RFI). ESD/Surge are a bit different.

There are quite some different standards covering different
requirement. Still IEC61000-4-x standards are often the base.
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_IEC_standards

Regards,
