Wow.  Broad question, that.  Can you narrow it down a bit?

At any rate, I went to a seminar about 8 months ago by
Kimmel and Gerke, and I'd recommend it.  Covered SI in
circuits and all manner of noise and immunity issues.

The short answer is &quot;Understand the noise and provide
it with as low impedance a path to ground as possible.&quot;

The long answer can be summarized in two to three eight
hour lectures.

Mike H.

