What I'd like to see is the sharing of experiences with EMI
(especically EFT/CI/RFI).

Let me start. My first job as a real electronics engineer
is to troubleshoot the EMI problem for a capacitive level
sensor in a metal housing. It failed EFT/CI/RFI as well as
ESD. After solving some other performance
related problems and two relayout, I managed to get the
sensor passed all the tests except RFI. Only then I started
to think about more on the design and I found out the problem
was related to a high bandwidth peak-dector. Adding a small
resistor solved the problem.

Xiaofan
